title: Independent candidate Abdul Munim wins PK-29 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 09 (APP): Independent candidate Abdul Munim has won the Khyber Pakhtunkhwa Assembly election from PK-29, Shnagla-II by securing 14,255 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Jamiat Ulema-e-Islam Pakistan (JUI-P) candidate Shaukat Ali who bagged 13,160 votes.
Overall votersâ€™ turn-out remained 31.83 per cent.
